        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "ci: split plugin ClawHub publishing paths",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- split plugin ClawHub publishing into a normal OIDC release path and a protected token bootstrap path\n- route root release candidates so trusted existing packages use the official ClawHub reusable publish workflow, while first-publish or trusted-publisher repair candidates use the bootstrap workflow\n- keep the normal ClawHub release workflow free of `CLAWHUB_TOKEN`, and keep the token scoped to the bootstrap workflow\n- pin the official ClawHub reusable publish workflow by SHA and pin the bootstrap CLI to `clawhub@0.21.0`\n- make bootstrap recovery idempotent when a package version was created before trusted-publisher setup completed\n\n## Verification\n\n- `actionlint .github/workflows/plugin-clawhub-release.yml .github/workflows/plugin-clawhub-new.yml .github/workflows/openclaw-release-publish.yml`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/plugin-clawhub-release.test.ts test/scripts/package-acceptance-workflow.test.ts test/scripts/release-beta-verifier.test.ts`\n- safe local CLI config smoke against `http://127.0.0.1:9`: `clawhub@0.21.0` read `{ registry, token }` from `CLAWHUB_CONFIG_PATH` and failed only at `fetch failed`, so no production state was touched\n- `AUTOREVIEW_AUTO_TESTS=0 /Users/patrickerichsen/.codex/worktrees/9173/clawhub/.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`\n\n## Review notes\n\n- `autoreview` reported clean: no accepted/actionable findings after the token-config, wait-gate, and trusted-publisher repair fixes.\n- The normal plugin ClawHub release workflow has no `CLAWHUB_TOKEN`; token auth is isolated to the bootstrap workflow guarded by the `clawhub-plugin-bootstrap` environment.\n",
